                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Turkey/837: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-28T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 28, 1943—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>856. Careful consideration had already been given in appropriate quarters to the
                    action proposed in your 1716, October 18, 11 a.m. and decision had been reached
                    that under known conditions it could produce no more than a brief interruption
                    of traffic. Upon receipt of your telegram, however, the proposal has been
                    presented for further study and is now under reconsideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
